14:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Artbreeder and Craiyon share a solid foundation of core features including Text To Image, Upscaling. Where Artbreeder pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Image To Image and Style Transfer and Commercial License, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Craiyon uniquely offers Batch Generation and Api Access, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Artbreeder holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 5/10, while Craiyon scores 4/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
15:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Artbreeder and Craiyon offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Artbreeder's free tier and Craiyon's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
